<pre><code class="language-python">if player.colliderect(plat) and velocity_y &gt; 0:
    player.bottom = plat.top
    velocity_y = 0
    on_ground = True
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Why check <code>velocity_y &gt; 0</code>? What does <code>player.bottom = plat.top</code> do?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-python">on_ground = False
for plat in platforms:
    if player.colliderect(plat) and velocity_y &gt; 0:
        ...
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Why is <code>on_ground</code> set to <code>False</code> <em>before</em> the loop, every frame?</strong></p>
