<h2>4 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>Read this working collision code carefully, then answer the questions about it.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">platforms = [
    pygame.Rect(0, 550, 800, 50),
    pygame.Rect(200, 450, 120, 20),
]

on_ground = False
for plat in platforms:
    if player.colliderect(plat) and velocity_y &gt; 0:
        player.bottom = plat.top
        velocity_y = 0
        on_ground = True
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Why are the platforms kept in a list instead of separate variables?</strong></p>
